In this article, President Trump gives remarks regarding the border wall and the ongoing government shutdown. He emphasizes the unity among Republicans and their support for border security. He claims that Mexico is indirectly paying for the wall through the USMCA trade deal. Trump also discusses the possibility of declaring a national emergency to fund the wall and criticizes the Democrats for not prioritizing border security. He addresses the media's portrayal of his meeting with Democratic leaders, denying claims of a temper tantrum. Trump mentions the formation of a new migrant caravan and emphasizes the need for a strong border wall. He concludes by expressing his willingness to make a compromise or declare a national emergency to end the shutdown.